Out of the hundred and 
twenty shares comprising this village,


to Viṣṇuśarman 
shall go twenty shares;

to his son Mādiśarman, twenty;

to Mahāsenaśarman, twenty;

to the latter’s dear younger brother Dāmaśarman, twenty;

to Mudokura-boya Gaṇaiśarman, six;

to Ātukuru-boya Viṣṇuśarman, five;

to Koṇḍasāmi-boya, five;

to Pāḍi-boya, one;

to Kumunūru-boya Mādiśarman, four;

to 
ndi-boya, two;

to Naḍukuḻi-boya Sarvaśarman, two;

to Veḷucaḷi-boya Bhaṭṭaśarman, two;

to Re
-boya, two;

to Kanpaṟ-boya Maṇḍaśarman, two;

to Revaśarman, two;

to Irukuṭūrur-boya, two.

First noticed in
30 A/1940-1941 39 . Edited from the original by H. K. Narasimhaswami (
) with a summary of the contents, estampages of the plates and a (poorly printed) photograph of the seal. The present edition by Dániel Balogh is based on a collation of Narasimhaswami's text with his published facsimiles.
